    "comprehension": null,
    "direction": null,
    "content": "<p>A germanium crystal is doped with arsenic atoms and indium atoms simultaneously. Number of arsenic atoms used $=5 \\times 10^{22}$ per $\\mathrm{m}^3$ and number of indium atoms used $=5 \\times 10^{20}$ per $\\mathrm{m}^3$, then resulting crystal is a/an</p>",
    "options": [
      {
        "identifier": "A",
        "content": " p-n junction\n"
      },
      {
        "identifier": "B",
        "content": " p-type semiconductor\n"
      },
      {
        "identifier": "C",
        "content": " $n$-type semiconductor\n"
      },
      {
        "identifier": "D",
        "content": " Depends on number of germanium atoms in given sample."
      }
    ],
    "correct_options": [
      "C"
    ],
    "answer": null,
    "explanation": "<p>Germanium is doped with two types of impurities:</p>\n\n\n<p><p>Arsenic (As) atoms act as donor impurities, which provide extra electrons and result in n-type doping.</p></p>\n<p><p>Indium (In) atoms act as acceptor impurities, which create holes and result in p-type doping.</p></p>\n\n\n<p>The number densities given are:</p>\n\n\n<p><p>Number of arsenic atoms: $$N_{As} = 5 \\times 10^{22} \\, \\text{per m}^3$$</p></p>\n<p><p>Number of indium atoms: $$N_{In} = 5 \\times 10^{20} \\, \\text{per m}^3$$</p></p>\n\n\n<p><p>When both dopants are added simultaneously, their effects tend to cancel each other partially. However, the net doping is determined by the difference between the donor concentration and the acceptor concentration:</p>\n<p>$$N_{\\text{net}} = N_{\\text{donors}} - N_{\\text{acceptors}} = 5 \\times 10^{22} - 5 \\times 10^{20}$$</p></p>\n<p><p>Since $$5 \\times 10^{22}$$ is much larger than $$5 \\times 10^{20}$$ (by a factor of 100), the donors dominate. Therefore, the net doping is n-type.</p></p>\n<p><p>As a result, the resulting germanium crystal is an n-type semiconductor.</p></p>\n\n<p>The correct answer is Option C: n-type semiconductor.</p>",
    "topic": null,
    "year": 2024,
    "yearKey": "viteee-2024",
    "difficulty": null
  },
