    "answer": null,
    "explanation": "<p>No. of electrons reducing the collector,</p>\n<p>$$n_c=\\frac{94}{100} \\times 10^{10}=0.94 \\times 10^{10}$$</p>\n<p>Emitter current, $$i_e=\\frac{n_e \\times e}{t}$$</p>\n<p>Collector current, $$i_c=\\frac{n_c \\times e}{t}$$</p>\n<p>Current transfer ratio,</p>\n<p>$$\\alpha=\\frac{i_c}{i_e}=\\frac{n_c}{n_e}=\\frac{0.94 \\times 10^{10}}{10^{10}}=0.94=\\alpha$$</p>",
